South African 4-year-old child star Sbahle Mzizi was recently named Favourite African Kidfluencer of the Year at this years Nickelodeon Kids Choice Awards.  To celebrate her wonderful achievement, Ntando threw a Nickelodeon Kids Choice Award party in honour of Sbahle and her award. Taking to social media, the television personality shared a series of pictures from the event where she is seen posing in a cat woman suit with her daughter, who was dressed in a blue long sleeve princess dress. In the caption of the post, Duma shared a small message to her daughter letting her know that she should always celebrate every single milestone in her life.  “Remember to celebrate milestones,” said Duma.  ALSO READ: PICS: Inside Natasha Thahane’s baby shower She then went on to say that she as well as her loved ones had a party to celebrate the dynamite that is her daughter, and also added how she tries her best to be a supportive and present mother in her daughter’s life. “Celebrated a dynamite that is my daughter. My biggest joy, love of my life and blessing. I’m a proud mother. A cool mother. A willing mother. A supportive and present mother,” said the actress. She ended off the caption by praying that God continues to give her the strength to raise the remarkable human being that her daughter is, and also stated that she is extremely proud of the child star.. “I pray to God that he continues to give me strength and wisdom in raising you into a different and remarkable human that you already are. “I love you with all my heart. @sbahlemzizi and I’m proud of you and I’m a proud mother of you,” said Duma.